{
  "stem": "20083.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Anthony Eden was a hunchbacked colonel who was very, very kind.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whenever we had any problems or needed anything, we could-- or his door was always open.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We could go to him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We really didn't need much because we had our own rooms, maybe two or three to a room, two or three refugees.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember I'd shared with somebody called Helmut Riehls and Harry Willing, or Harold Swilling, as he was called originally.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we really had a wonderful life because most of the time we did-- simply, we kept our hotel clean, because we were stationed in Isle of Man hotels.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the rest of the time, we could either go swimming, or we could play tennis.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we had the full facilities of a luxury vacation resort without paying a penny for it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Afterwards-- we stayed for about two or three months, as I said.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in 1940.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were interned in 1940, right after the fall of France.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I was finally released, I could go-- first, I went to a youth hostel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in this youth hostel in Evesham, we were treated extremely well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a wonderful time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And finally, also, I could-- later on, at least-- go and spend some time with my sponsor, Sir Eustace Pulbrook, the chairman of Lloyd's of London.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I really did not have to suffer very much in England during the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But later on, after my youth hostel experiences, when I went to London, first, I stayed in a place called King Henry's Road.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, later, in Camden Town in-- on Camden Road.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, these were youth hostels specially for German and Austrian refugees like me, youngsters like me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In London, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
